Doc Spatz,<br><br>
I feel you may be over-reacting to this individual's offer.<br><br>
I do not personally agree with the manner in which the offer of assistance is presented with &quot;conditions&quot; and I do not share the philosophy advocated. There is, however, an inherent right to freedom of expression here.<br><br>
For better or for worse, I did fight for the concept of freedom of expression for the Vietnamese people in the Vietnam War. Such was my charge and oath. The present opression of the Vietnamese people by their government is no different than that which you expressed be done here:<br><br>
&quot;Take your &quot;mission&quot; and your narrow minded &quot;burn em at the stake&quot; religion and go where you belong, cause you don't belong here.&quot;<br><br>
&quot;I guess the nuts will be crawling out of the woodwork after the CNN coverage. Please get out the Raid Can and remove this crud.&quot;<br><br>
There really is no difference between your positions here and the inhumane and barbaric treatment of dissenters by the &quot;peoples republic&quot;.<br><br>
I took the time to visit their web site. They believe in what they say as strongly as do I in my beliefs. Their intentions are well meaning in the context of their belief structure and philosophy. There may be some people who might derive personal benefit from their teachings. <br><br>
As a Vietnam Veteran who has fought for freedom of expression, and everything else we find dear and most frequently take for granted, I strongly urge you to reconsider your position.<br><br>
An apology might be in order.<br><br>
Thank you,<br><br>
